                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d498">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">121.5532/11: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-12-06T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 6, 1930—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>95. Your 162, December 5, 3 p.m. Informally advised by Navy Department that
                    Lieutenant Commander Blandy will be detailed as Naval Attaché to the Embassy,
                    effective February 1st on expiration of his services with Naval Mission.</p>
                <p>Please inquire of Brazilian Government whether designation of Blandy as Naval
                    Attaché is agreeable. Cable reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
